parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure and Premature Wear of Connecting Rod Bearings
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine and premature wear of connecting rod bearings can cause the vehicle to lose motive power, stall, or seize, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses motive power
stalls
or seizes; loud knocking or banging sounds from the engine; abnormal vibrations or shaking; burning odor inside the vehicle; warning lights illuminated
including the check engine and hybrid system warning lights.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the knock sensor can cause the engine to misfire, leading to a loss of power, stalling, or engine failure, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power; warning lights illuminated
including the check engine warning light; knocking or pinging sounds from the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hybrid system can cause the vehicle to lose motive power, stall, or seize, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses motive power
stalls
or seizes; warning lights illuminated
including the hybrid system warning light; abnormal vibrations or shaking; loud noises from the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EGR pipe can cause the engine to misfire, leading to a loss of power, stalling, or engine failure, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power; warning lights illuminated
including the check engine warning light; unusual sounds or noises from the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the HPCU module can cause the vehicle to lose motive power, stall, or seize, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses motive power
stalls
or seizes; warning lights illuminated
including the hybrid system warning light; abnormal vibrations or shaking; loud noises from the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or experience various warning lights and errors, leading to potential safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
warning lights illuminate
the vehicle shifts into Limp Mode
the accelerator pedal assembly fails
the generator pulley grinds
the belt slips
and the dashboard lights up with multiple errors.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Power Relay Assembly and Battery Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power relay assembly and battery can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to potential safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
and the power relay assembly and battery need to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or experience difficulty shifting gears, leading to potential safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle shifts into Limp Mode.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in recall repairs can cause inconvenience and potential safety risks if the issue is not addressed promptly.
symptoms: The dealer informs the contact that the recall repair will take several months
and the manufacturer offers an alternative solution.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of advanced safety features can cause a lack of warning or malfunction, leading to potential safety risks.
symptoms: The front side collision warning system fails to function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the HEV system can cause the vehicle to refuse to start, display error messages, and experience sudden loss of power while driving, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle refuses to start
displays error messages such as "Check HEV System"
loss of power while driving
sudden deceleration
and inability to accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of power and acceleration can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Abrupt and total loss of acceleration at full throttle
sudden power loss at high RPM shift points
sudden surging of the vehicle after the power loss condition has cleared
and unreliable drivetrain response.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Inability to fully engage the brakes
sudden deceleration
and display of error messages such as "Stop Vehicle and Check Brakes".
